WEBVTT

00:00.898 --> 00:02.099
WOMAN: <i>Previously on</i> Underground...

00:02.166 --> 00:03.601
We have to go now!

00:03.666 --> 00:04.936
No, we can't, we got the plan.

00:05.437 --> 00:07.438
(GURGLES)

00:07.504 --> 00:09.439
TOM: <i>I've never had a runaway before.</i>

00:09.506 --> 00:11.508
If my paddy rollers haven't
retrieved them by nightfall,

00:11.574 --> 00:12.843
consider yourself hired.

00:12.910 --> 00:14.512
There's a train leaving north
from Atlanta tomorrow.

00:14.579 --> 00:16.014
What you telling me for?

00:16.079 --> 00:18.383
ERNESTINE: <i>Do what you can to
get my daughter on that train.</i>

00:20.597 --> 00:21.843
Run!

00:21.910 --> 00:22.852
TOM: Get water!

00:22.920 --> 00:24.255
Now!

00:24.746 --> 00:26.722
Where Pearly Mae? My brother?

00:28.293 --> 00:29.526
(PANTING)

00:34.485 --> 00:37.136
TOM: <i>Wanted, seven escaped slaves.</i>

00:37.200 --> 00:39.436
Negro man named Noah.

00:39.502 --> 00:43.207
<i>Six feet high, dark
complexion, tattooed body.</i>

00:43.273 --> 00:45.475
<i>Very smart. The ringleader.</i>

00:45.541 --> 00:46.810
Negro man named Zeke.

00:46.877 --> 00:50.048
<i>Six-foot-five-inches.
Pushing 300 pounds.</i>

00:50.114 --> 00:52.083
<i>Should be considered very dangerous.</i>

00:53.517 --> 00:56.121
<i>Negro man named Cato.</i>

00:56.187 --> 00:59.524
Five-foot-eight, copper toned,
fanciful dress.

00:59.590 --> 01:02.293
<i>Horribly burned across
the right side of his face.</i>

01:02.359 --> 01:04.358
Negro man named Moses.

01:04.628 --> 01:05.996
<i>Five-foot-ten-inches.</i>

01:06.062 --> 01:07.698
<i>Very affable continence.</i>

01:07.765 --> 01:10.935
<i>Most likely carrying a Negro
child, Boo, seven years of age.</i>

01:11.000 --> 01:12.713
Negro boy named Henry.

01:12.779 --> 01:14.871
<i>About 15 years of age. Skinny.</i>

01:14.938 --> 01:16.006
<i>Talkative.</i>

01:17.173 --> 01:18.910
Negro girl named Rosalee.

01:18.976 --> 01:20.911
Mulatto.

01:20.977 --> 01:22.946
<i>Delicate nature. Well made.</i>

01:23.014 --> 01:26.083
<i>Wearing a fancy dress upon escape.</i>

01:26.149 --> 01:29.720
<i>♪ The world is waiting,
finding freedom...  ♪</i>

01:29.786 --> 01:33.190
For every runaway confined
to the Georgia County Jail

01:33.258 --> 01:35.125
or delivered to the Macon Plantation,

01:35.193 --> 01:37.729
a reward of $1,000

01:37.794 --> 01:40.531
plus reasonable expenses
will be promptly paid.

01:41.265 --> 01:43.000
Dead or alive.

01:43.066 --> 01:45.369
<i>♪ But you know I know</i>

01:45.435 --> 01:47.804
<i>♪ We were born to die alone</i>

01:47.872 --> 01:49.374
<i>♪ Die alone ♪</i>

01:51.809 --> 01:55.078
<i>♪ The wolf howls out</i>

01:55.146 --> 01:58.649
<i>♪ As he drags you to the grave</i>

01:58.715 --> 02:02.619
<i>♪ The devil's dream</i>

02:02.685 --> 02:05.122
<i>♪ Haunts you on the way</i>

02:05.188 --> 02:08.824
<i>♪ Now, one day Jesus' hand</i>

02:08.893 --> 02:12.330
<i>♪ Will lead us to the promised land</i>

02:12.395 --> 02:15.799
<i>♪ One day we will stand</i>

02:15.866 --> 02:18.536
<i>♪ Rejoice in victory</i>

02:18.603 --> 02:20.604
<i>♪ We fall down</i>

02:20.670 --> 02:21.938
<i>♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh</i>

02:22.006 --> 02:24.108
<i>♪ To look up</i>

02:24.174 --> 02:25.375
<i>♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh</i>

02:25.442 --> 02:29.013
<i>♪ Waiting to see</i>

02:29.079 --> 02:31.749
<i>♪ Heaven's door ♪</i>

