02:59.943 --> 03:01.345
They stopped here.

03:02.146 --> 03:03.882
You see the tracks?

03:03.948 --> 03:05.849
BEN: They're not in a
straight line any more.

03:05.916 --> 03:07.518
They're all a mess.

03:07.585 --> 03:08.953
Not a mess.

03:09.920 --> 03:12.089
Look careful at each set.

03:12.156 --> 03:14.724
Direction, intensity.

03:14.792 --> 03:16.593
All together, they tell a story.

03:16.661 --> 03:18.429
Hey, I need to rest.

03:18.495 --> 03:19.630
CATO: There ain't no resting.

03:19.697 --> 03:20.997
There's running
and there's being caught.

03:21.065 --> 03:22.699
Now get your ass up, old man.

03:22.765 --> 03:23.901
Let me carry her a while.

03:23.967 --> 03:25.235
Don't touch her!

03:26.237 --> 03:29.006
You said there was a plan. A map.

03:29.073 --> 03:30.742
Next Sunday we was supposed to go.

03:30.807 --> 03:31.976
MOSES: Then you just gonna leave us.

03:32.043 --> 03:33.378
I had no choice.

03:33.443 --> 03:35.479
You had a choice. And you choose her.

03:38.782 --> 03:40.484
AUGUST: <i>I count seven.</i>

03:40.551 --> 03:41.985
The five who used the fire
as a distraction

03:42.053 --> 03:43.788
must have met up
with the two who ran earlier.

03:43.854 --> 03:45.822
Is seven runaways a lot?

03:45.889 --> 03:47.824
More than I've ever seen.

03:47.892 --> 03:49.561
And they're all working together?

03:50.728 --> 03:52.930
Up to here, anyhow.

03:52.996 --> 03:56.299
See the skids, broken branches?

03:56.366 --> 03:57.567
There was a fight.

03:57.634 --> 03:59.402
Now, we all sorry
what done happen Pearly Mae...

03:59.470 --> 04:00.871
Ain't got no use for your sympathy!

04:00.937 --> 04:02.072
I trusted you.

04:02.139 --> 04:03.573
Now my family's torn apart.

04:03.639 --> 04:06.009
- Let go of him!
- They got my Pearly Mae. They got her!

04:06.077 --> 04:07.345
God know what they doing to her!

04:07.412 --> 04:09.080
Stop it! You scaring Boo.

04:12.650 --> 04:14.285
I'm sorry, sorry.

04:14.352 --> 04:16.887
Noah, that slave catcher and
his son could be on our tails.

04:16.954 --> 04:18.622
We too exposed in this daylight.

04:18.689 --> 04:20.992
We have to find some place
to hide, wait till nightfall.

04:21.057 --> 04:23.593
So we can continue star gazing?

04:23.661 --> 04:25.196
Find ourselves the blue haze?

04:25.262 --> 04:27.029
Ain't none of us got any idea
what the hell any of that means.

04:27.096 --> 04:29.432
You got any better ideas on how to
run other than running, we all ears.

04:29.500 --> 04:32.069
Well, I'm glad you finally asked.

04:32.135 --> 04:33.437
Tell me what you see here.

04:36.774 --> 04:38.122
I ain't sure, sir.

04:38.188 --> 04:39.877
Changed course.

04:39.944 --> 04:42.380
They ain't just running
to escape no more,

04:42.447 --> 04:44.115
they running to something.

04:44.180 --> 04:45.848
- What's east?
- CATO: <i>A train.</i>

04:45.916 --> 04:47.517
Northbound. Out of Atlanta.

04:47.584 --> 04:49.433
Ain't no way in hell you could
know something like that.

04:49.500 --> 04:51.355
Her momma the one told me.
Said it'd be leaving today.

04:51.421 --> 04:53.523
Look, I don't know what your angle
is, but we sticking to the plan.

04:53.591 --> 04:56.461
- Oh, so now we "sticking to the plan?"
- NOAH: Hey!

04:56.528 --> 04:58.529
We ain't on the plantation no more.

04:58.596 --> 04:59.997
You ain't driving nothing round here.

05:00.062 --> 05:01.899
I'm the one who got the lion's
share of us off Macon.

05:04.868 --> 05:07.103
I'm going for that train.

05:07.170 --> 05:09.873
Ain't like we can just walk
into the city and buy tickets.

05:09.940 --> 05:12.009
I might be I know
somebody who could help.

05:13.478 --> 05:14.545
(EXHALES)

05:24.191 --> 05:25.625
Let's get a move on.

05:25.777 --> 05:26.979
We ain't that far behind.

05:54.325 --> 05:56.227
Now, this is a surprise.

05:56.292 --> 05:59.062
I had no idea you knew
where this nursery was.

05:59.128 --> 06:00.131
Give us the room.

06:01.698 --> 06:02.833
Now.

06:06.737 --> 06:08.006
(SIGHS)

06:08.172 --> 06:10.643
You've got all the slaves
out in that ruined field,

06:10.794 --> 06:13.397
I barely have any help
in this house as it is,

06:13.636 --> 06:15.404
and now you're dismissing them, too.

06:18.181 --> 06:20.551
(SOFTLY) This was
an attack on our family.

06:20.617 --> 06:22.352
Who knows how long
they'd been planning this...

06:22.419 --> 06:23.755
- ... how many were involved.
- Oh, please...

06:23.821 --> 06:25.890
... be more dramatic.

06:25.955 --> 06:28.893
When Daddy was in charge
they'd run off all the time

06:28.960 --> 06:30.762
and be dragged right back.

06:30.828 --> 06:33.429
It's just a facet of Southern life.

06:33.825 --> 06:34.999
These things happen.

06:35.064 --> 06:36.380
Not to me.

06:36.833 --> 06:39.536
This whole mess could not have come
at a worse time for my campaign,

06:39.604 --> 06:41.614
especially with the
reverend arriving soon.

06:42.273 --> 06:45.008
Now, I put a substantial reward
on those runners' heads,

06:45.075 --> 06:47.311
but there's not much more
I can do from here.

06:47.378 --> 06:49.180
Pearly Mae knows
where those runners went.

06:49.246 --> 06:51.215
She could help us catch 'em
sooner rather than later.

06:51.282 --> 06:53.417
So sick the paddy rollers on her.

06:53.484 --> 06:54.486
I have.

06:55.453 --> 06:57.088
She hasn't uttered a word.

06:57.155 --> 06:59.190
Now, I plan to talk to every
slave on this plantation,

06:59.256 --> 07:01.391
but Pearly Mae is the key.

07:03.361 --> 07:05.729
(SIGHS)

07:05.796 --> 07:08.600
Now, you share certain things
in common with her.

07:09.934 --> 07:11.314
You're both mothers.

07:11.936 --> 07:13.705
You're both born on this plantation.

07:14.972 --> 07:16.039
And...

07:17.140 --> 07:19.242
and I... (SIGHS)

07:19.309 --> 07:21.042
I would appreciate...

07:21.778 --> 07:25.449
... any insight you have
on how to get her to crack.

07:47.356 --> 07:48.726
I ain't seen any moving around inside.

07:48.949 --> 07:50.407
You sure this his place?

07:50.475 --> 07:52.309
Well, I ain't been here
since I was sold to Macon.

07:52.376 --> 07:53.544
Could be he gone.

07:53.611 --> 07:55.204
You okay?

07:55.847 --> 07:57.648
It ain't your fault,
what happened to Pearly Mae.

07:57.715 --> 08:00.251
We got to get on that train,
for Boo's sake.

08:01.652 --> 08:02.652
We going in.

08:02.720 --> 08:04.554
Moses, Cato, you're with me.

08:04.621 --> 08:05.756
I ain't taking Boo in there.

08:05.823 --> 08:07.024
You most certainly ain't.

08:07.090 --> 08:08.391
You the one know the man the best.

08:08.458 --> 08:09.793
He might not help less you with us.

08:09.861 --> 08:11.829
I ain't leaving my baby behind.

08:11.895 --> 08:13.698
You want to help her? This is how.

08:13.763 --> 08:14.997
I got her.

08:15.064 --> 08:16.400
Henry, Zeke with me,

08:16.467 --> 08:18.536
case anything happen,
anyways. Come on, baby.

08:19.837 --> 08:21.072
Come on.

08:33.616 --> 08:35.352
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

08:35.419 --> 08:36.892
MAN: I'm coming already.

08:40.357 --> 08:41.592
(GRUNTS)

08:41.659 --> 08:43.995
We don't mean you no harm.

08:44.062 --> 08:45.296
I knew I should have stayed away

08:45.362 --> 08:47.131
when you come at me for paper.

08:47.197 --> 08:48.799
You want us gone? You tell us how we

08:48.866 --> 08:50.467
get on that train leaving Atlanta today.

08:50.534 --> 08:52.102
Hey, now, that's tricky stuff.

08:52.169 --> 08:54.137
No, it got to be a way that don't
involve sneaking in the city.

08:54.204 --> 08:55.705
MOSES: You used to be a railroad man.

08:55.772 --> 08:57.607
If anybody know, figure it's you.

08:57.674 --> 09:01.245
Well, maybe I can help,
but everything got a price.

09:01.312 --> 09:03.347
We ain't got nothing
to trade but your hide.

09:03.414 --> 09:05.082
Now, that ain't at all true.

09:05.147 --> 09:06.383
We got a old revolver.

09:06.451 --> 09:07.585
From a collector.

09:07.651 --> 09:09.152
I helped procure it myself.

09:09.219 --> 09:10.620
- What kind of revolver?
- It ain't for trade.

09:10.688 --> 09:12.021
Everything's for trade.

09:12.088 --> 09:14.725
Oh, well, maybe I use it once,
before I give it up then.

09:16.961 --> 09:18.096
(GRUNTS)

09:19.496 --> 09:21.198
Now, we give you this here,

09:21.265 --> 09:22.634
you get us on that train.

09:41.385 --> 09:42.687
(CLANKING)

09:54.164 --> 09:56.467
Someone ought to take her some water.

09:56.534 --> 09:58.535
She don't deserve a drop of nothing.

09:58.602 --> 10:01.838
Life gonna be harder for all of
us 'cause of that woman and hers.

10:01.905 --> 10:03.607
I hear the rollers
working over the lot of us.

10:05.108 --> 10:06.944
They taking folks out behind the shed.

10:07.911 --> 10:09.615
Even <i>massa</i> in on it.

10:10.180 --> 10:11.848
He don't never get his hands bloody.

10:11.915 --> 10:13.684
Seem like life gonna
change for all of us.

10:13.751 --> 10:15.653
Still, that woman there lost her child.

10:15.718 --> 10:17.088
She deserves some mercy.

10:19.589 --> 10:21.425
Don't be stupid, now.

10:27.497 --> 10:29.066
Watch yourself, boy.

11:04.093 --> 11:05.835
FROG JACK: Train y'all looking to catch leaves Atlanta

11:05.860 --> 11:06.953
a quarter past 5:00.

11:06.996 --> 11:09.165
It's just shy of three hours away.

11:09.232 --> 11:11.600
Right now, she about...

11:11.666 --> 11:13.802
... here. In two hours' time,

11:13.869 --> 11:15.304
she hits the switch

11:15.371 --> 11:16.439
just outside of town.

11:16.506 --> 11:18.241
Now, that's when she slows down,

11:18.307 --> 11:20.809
exposing her ass
like a two-dollar hooker.

11:20.877 --> 11:23.212
So that's how you get all this
junk, stealing from the trains.

11:23.278 --> 11:25.080
This is good, okay?

11:25.147 --> 11:27.316
It's still think in the woods.
We have enough cover to slip on.

11:27.382 --> 11:28.785
Timing's tough.

11:28.852 --> 11:30.387
That's where I lost my leg.

11:33.922 --> 11:35.825
(BOO HUMMING)

11:42.464 --> 11:43.700
(SIGHS)

11:53.075 --> 11:54.944
Now, baby, you got such pretty hair,

11:55.011 --> 11:56.913
you don't want to be
pulling it out, now.

11:58.281 --> 11:59.748
Let me see.

11:59.815 --> 12:01.317
You like this?

12:02.051 --> 12:03.552
Here, let me see.

12:06.655 --> 12:08.391
That's much better.

12:09.624 --> 12:11.594
(CONTINUES HUMMING SOFTLY)

12:12.427 --> 12:13.562
(SIGHS)

12:53.636 --> 12:55.505
They're inside.

12:55.570 --> 12:56.906
Hand me your rifle.

13:03.146 --> 13:05.048
We ain't gonna shoot 'em, are we?

13:05.113 --> 13:08.283
Ain't Mr. Macon say it's double
if we bring 'em back alive?

13:08.350 --> 13:10.052
That's just for the girl.

13:12.320 --> 13:14.055
But the goal...

13:14.123 --> 13:15.925
... is to...

13:15.990 --> 13:18.460
... always bring the property
back intact if you can.

13:21.263 --> 13:24.166
I want you to skinny
out back to the trees.

13:24.233 --> 13:27.235
Make a wide and quiet loop
around in front of the house.

13:27.302 --> 13:29.138
Once you're square with that front door,

13:30.440 --> 13:31.940
I want you to fire right inside.

13:32.007 --> 13:34.477
Right into it, three separate times.
You hear?

13:35.511 --> 13:36.713
Yes, sir.

13:38.248 --> 13:39.292
Why?

13:39.317 --> 13:41.117
It'll send 'em coming
out the back door my way,

13:41.182 --> 13:42.484
so I can pick 'em off.

13:44.420 --> 13:46.354
Now, keep a good distance,

13:46.421 --> 13:47.623
wide as you can.

13:51.727 --> 13:53.491
They come back your way,

13:53.930 --> 13:55.498
I want you to aim square for the chest.

13:55.565 --> 13:56.965
You understand me, son?

13:58.100 --> 13:59.101
Yes, sir.

14:24.126 --> 14:25.528
(DOOR OPENS)

14:34.170 --> 14:35.839
What you doing that for?

14:39.084 --> 14:40.927
Please, just tell me what's going on.

14:42.210 --> 14:44.046
<i>Massa</i> say we ain't
supposed to talk to you.

14:45.647 --> 14:47.264
And he say you can't be in here!

14:47.983 --> 14:50.319
Miss Ernestine, <i>massa</i>
was very clear on that.

14:50.386 --> 14:51.838
You're gonna keep your mouth shut.

14:52.387 --> 14:53.522
Unless you want Miss Suzanna to find out

14:53.589 --> 14:54.656
you've been stretching all her clothes,

14:54.723 --> 14:55.833
playing dress up in the mirror.

14:56.858 --> 14:58.493
Now, get to dusting that hallway.

14:58.560 --> 14:59.995
Let me know when anyone come this way.

15:04.566 --> 15:06.034
Come on, now.

15:07.402 --> 15:09.772
They want you cleaned up.
That's all we know.

15:15.411 --> 15:17.446
(SOBBING)

15:23.218 --> 15:24.587
You let it out.

15:25.653 --> 15:27.355
Ain't no shame in these tears.

15:27.422 --> 15:29.825
The sacrifice you made
for your daughter...

15:29.892 --> 15:31.761
... you should be proud of that.

15:31.826 --> 15:34.029
I don't know if it's gonna be enough.
(SNIFFLES)

15:38.434 --> 15:40.373
I remember when Boo was born.

15:42.104 --> 15:44.539
The day I helped her into this world.

15:44.607 --> 15:46.642
You remember how she was hollering?

15:46.709 --> 15:49.378
- She was kicking and screaming like the devil.
- (CHUCKLING)

15:50.012 --> 15:51.247
Hmm. (SNIFFLES)

15:52.281 --> 15:54.050
She was strong then.

15:54.891 --> 15:56.585
And she's strong now.

15:57.766 --> 15:59.361
And God'll help her to freedom.

16:01.357 --> 16:03.059
I don't believe in God.

16:04.493 --> 16:05.827
I never have.

16:09.031 --> 16:11.066
But I believe in my Moses.

16:19.742 --> 16:22.712
<i>♪ This little bit ♪</i>

16:23.778 --> 16:27.816
<i>♪ Of stardust ♪</i>

16:27.883 --> 16:30.952
<i>♪ Keeps waking me up ♪</i>

16:31.020 --> 16:32.021
(GUN COCKS)

16:32.086 --> 16:35.923
<i>♪ All in my head ♪</i>

16:35.990 --> 16:39.995
<i>♪ Tongue tied in knots ♪</i>

16:40.061 --> 16:42.632
<i>♪ Keeps shutting me out ♪</i>

16:44.166 --> 16:46.802
<i>♪ Just let me out ♪</i>

16:48.270 --> 16:50.940
<i>♪ I wanna run... ♪</i>

17:00.315 --> 17:03.752
<i>♪ Just let me out...  ♪</i>

17:06.788 --> 17:07.990
(CLICKS)

17:11.760 --> 17:12.961
No, they're flushing you out!

17:13.027 --> 17:14.329
They're flushing you out!

17:15.631 --> 17:16.632
(GRUNTS)

17:24.605 --> 17:26.307
Why the hell you shooting at us?

17:26.374 --> 17:28.743
$1,000 times seven, that's why.

17:28.809 --> 17:30.878
- There's a price on your head. Dead or alive.
- (GRUNTING)

17:30.946 --> 17:33.116
They calling y'all the Macon Seven.

17:38.354 --> 17:39.455
(GUN CLICKING)

17:50.999 --> 17:53.635
Look at what we found
down here in the dirt.

18:00.956 --> 18:02.724
You ain't think this through, Jack!

18:02.791 --> 18:05.761
A gimp against the three of us.
Two and a half.

18:05.828 --> 18:07.562
I saw I got Moses.

18:11.933 --> 18:13.768
Hey, what's inside these?

18:13.834 --> 18:15.470
There's got to be something we can use.

18:16.504 --> 18:17.606
I don't know!

18:17.671 --> 18:18.972
CATO: I knew it!

18:19.040 --> 18:20.642
This one-eyed bastard can't read!

18:20.708 --> 18:21.743
How you know the freedom song?

18:21.810 --> 18:24.111
Pearly Mae. She the one that can read.

18:24.178 --> 18:25.846
(GUNSHOT)

18:25.914 --> 18:28.250
You done pick one hell of a team.

18:30.485 --> 18:31.653
(GUNSHOT)

18:33.321 --> 18:35.055
Y'all still alive in there?

18:35.122 --> 18:37.024
Not that it matters.

18:37.091 --> 18:39.160
- My pockets get lined either way.
- (GUN COCKS)

18:39.227 --> 18:40.495
(SHOUTS)

18:41.129 --> 18:42.865
(BOTH GRUNTING)

18:44.398 --> 18:45.935
NOAH: Let's get out of here.

18:47.601 --> 18:49.804
The whole time you been
tracking them Macon runaways,

18:49.870 --> 18:51.340
we've been tracking you.

18:51.407 --> 18:53.809
Shit, I thought you'd seen us
back at that fallen tree.

18:53.876 --> 18:55.043
(GRUNTING)

19:00.648 --> 19:02.083
(SOFTLY) Please...

19:02.149 --> 19:04.119
- BEN: Let him go!
- (GUN CLICKS)

19:07.656 --> 19:09.558
You ain't gonna shoot all of us.

19:10.359 --> 19:11.360
No, sir.

19:12.526 --> 19:13.761
Just you.

19:15.796 --> 19:17.765
All right, kid, relax.

19:17.831 --> 19:20.201
We's just finishin' up
with the old man anyway.

19:21.503 --> 19:23.438
With interest, I reckon that one

19:23.504 --> 19:26.841
runaway you stole from us
has ballooned into seven.

19:26.908 --> 19:28.475
Pick up your hunt.

19:28.542 --> 19:30.411
I think that makes us about even.

19:45.092 --> 19:46.427
PEARLY MAE: <i>They done beat me.</i>

19:46.494 --> 19:48.196
Strung me up.

19:48.263 --> 19:51.000
Now they dress me
up real pretty like y'all.

19:51.934 --> 19:53.434
Why they doing this?

19:53.501 --> 19:55.738
<i>Massa</i> probably gonna take
you down to his office.

19:57.604 --> 20:00.308
Probably have a feast waiting for you.

20:00.375 --> 20:02.511
Make you a nice cocktail.

20:03.544 --> 20:05.046
Something sweet.

20:05.112 --> 20:06.581
'Cause you're a woman.

20:06.648 --> 20:08.882
Then he gonna sit down and talk to you

20:08.949 --> 20:11.085
like you've been the best
of friends for years.

20:11.152 --> 20:13.887
Ain't nothing gonna make me
tell them where they went.

20:13.955 --> 20:16.391
I ain't gonna have them
draggin' my baby back here.

20:17.325 --> 20:20.361
It ain't as easy as saying no.

20:20.428 --> 20:23.131
<i>Massa</i> wants to be liked, appreciated.

20:23.197 --> 20:25.033
(SOFTLY) You got to be grateful.

20:25.100 --> 20:26.802
Eat everything on your plate.

20:27.802 --> 20:29.370
And that drink,

20:29.437 --> 20:30.906
when you sip it,

20:30.972 --> 20:32.974
ask what's in it.

20:33.041 --> 20:35.210
Listen real good to his answer.

20:35.276 --> 20:36.578
Make him feel heard.

20:37.579 --> 20:40.616
Then you tell him
they heading for the swamps.

20:40.681 --> 20:41.916
Give him his win,

20:41.983 --> 20:43.619
and all this will all blow over.

20:45.187 --> 20:46.854
<i>Massa</i> looking for you, Stine.

20:46.921 --> 20:48.723
Told him I'd get you from the cookhouse.

20:50.391 --> 20:51.759
You got to stay strong.

20:51.827 --> 20:53.395
For both our daughters' sake.

20:57.866 --> 21:00.569
I know firsthand how <i>massa</i>
get what he wants.

21:12.379 --> 21:13.448
Sit down.

21:14.049 --> 21:15.417
Go on, now.

21:22.756 --> 21:24.058
TOM: Sam?

21:25.761 --> 21:27.796
I need you to tell me what I don't know.

21:27.861 --> 21:29.196
(STAMMERS)

21:29.264 --> 21:30.599
Beg your pardon, <i>massa?</i>

21:34.335 --> 21:37.205
I've spoken to nearly
every field slave I own.

21:38.206 --> 21:40.641
And all I got was petty gossip.

21:40.708 --> 21:42.744
Tellin' me Moses preaching.

21:44.244 --> 21:46.548
Noah thick as thieves
with that stable boy.

21:47.716 --> 21:49.685
Rosalee went over to Lily Shaw's.

21:49.752 --> 21:51.418
Like I don't know my own plantation.

21:51.485 --> 21:54.155
Do I seem like a man who does
not know his own plantation?

21:54.222 --> 21:55.858
(SHAKILY) No, sir. No, sir.

21:57.559 --> 21:58.827
(WINGS FLAPPING)

21:58.894 --> 22:00.328
(GUNSHOT ECHOES)

22:00.395 --> 22:01.930
(FLAPPING STOPS)

22:07.235 --> 22:08.637
How'd I miss this?

22:09.271 --> 22:10.608
Seven of 'em...

22:11.238 --> 22:13.207
... all conspiring against me?

22:17.044 --> 22:19.906
Don't nobody know nobody else's heart.

22:20.982 --> 22:23.185
It was my own sister,
and I didn't even know.

22:25.687 --> 22:27.145
People surprise you.

22:27.856 --> 22:29.784
Sometimes, you even surprise yourself.

22:31.091 --> 22:32.427
You think you one way...

22:34.128 --> 22:35.964
... then you find out you ain't.

22:40.267 --> 22:41.736
You're too clever
to be out in those fields.

22:41.803 --> 22:44.439
I'm going to get you back in that
shop soon, where you belong.

22:46.975 --> 22:48.542
Mmm.

22:48.610 --> 22:51.446
My daddy, he had two ways
of blowing off steam,

22:51.512 --> 22:53.683
drinking and shooting.

22:54.648 --> 22:56.818
I suppose he only meant to teach me one.

22:56.885 --> 22:58.076
But...

22:59.053 --> 23:01.456
... we do as we see,
not as we're told, don't we?

23:02.890 --> 23:04.258
You want to give it a try?

23:06.927 --> 23:08.397
Come on, yeah, come here.

23:16.838 --> 23:18.874
Now, it's all about patience, all right?

23:20.375 --> 23:22.945
You're gonna track
the bird with your gun.

23:24.346 --> 23:25.414
Anticipate...

23:26.281 --> 23:27.750
... then execute.

23:31.453 --> 23:32.654
(SIGHS)

23:50.104 --> 23:51.271
(LAUGHS)

23:51.339 --> 23:52.908
Hot damn, Sam, you just missed it.

23:57.279 --> 23:58.680
(PANTING)

24:12.260 --> 24:13.395
- (TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS)
- It's coming.

24:13.462 --> 24:14.830
Look.

24:15.964 --> 24:17.599
We can't let 'em see us
get on this train.

24:17.666 --> 24:18.966
Means we gotta time it just right.

24:19.033 --> 24:20.534
We wait for the last car,

24:20.601 --> 24:21.936
just before it speed back up.

24:22.003 --> 24:24.173
Now get your wind. Get ready.

24:25.306 --> 24:26.574
(PANTING)

24:26.975 --> 24:28.543
(SIGHS)

24:28.610 --> 24:30.312
You see something you like, house girl?

24:31.078 --> 24:32.181
They found us.

24:33.581 --> 24:34.850
What do we do now?

24:39.521 --> 24:40.789
Noah...

24:40.856 --> 24:42.190
Um, um, um...

24:42.256 --> 24:44.491
We... we... we head to Atlanta. Okay?

24:44.559 --> 24:46.261
Do whatever we gotta do
to get to the train there.

24:46.327 --> 24:47.695
Ain't no way we outrun a train.

24:47.762 --> 24:49.129
It's got to stop in the city.

24:49.196 --> 24:50.599
Now, Frog Jack said
it don't leave till 5:00.

24:50.665 --> 24:51.933
Give us just an hour to catch it.

24:51.998 --> 24:52.999
We go for that train now,

24:53.067 --> 24:54.235
them catchers be on us in no time.

24:54.302 --> 24:55.337
No, we split up.

24:55.402 --> 24:56.771
No. It's me and Henry.

24:56.838 --> 24:58.674
You and Zeke.
We go in opposite directions,

24:58.739 --> 24:59.841
we'll draw them away from you.

24:59.908 --> 25:01.274
Rosalee'll help you
get her to the train.

25:01.394 --> 25:02.643
Now, there's a water tower
on the edge of the city

25:02.710 --> 25:03.812
I seen. You can't miss it.

25:03.879 --> 25:04.913
We go there, we meet there.

25:04.979 --> 25:06.081
All right? Ready? Go!

25:08.248 --> 25:10.284
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)

25:10.351 --> 25:12.420
MAN: There they are! Get on 'em!

25:17.158 --> 25:18.260
(PANTING)

25:24.098 --> 25:25.300
Damn.

25:33.742 --> 25:34.976
(PANTING)

25:37.477 --> 25:39.446
They'll just run us down
if we follow the bank.

25:39.514 --> 25:40.716
We could take 'em together.

25:41.750 --> 25:42.951
(GUN COCKS)

25:43.017 --> 25:44.951
(PANTING) There ain't gonna be no we.

25:45.019 --> 25:46.922
- (GUNSHOT)
- (ZEKE SCREAMS)

25:47.254 --> 25:48.723
No!

25:48.790 --> 25:50.058
(PANTING)

25:53.794 --> 25:55.796
Come on. Come on, come on, come on.

25:57.130 --> 25:58.565
Gotcha now, big boy.

25:58.632 --> 26:00.167
Don't you give us no trouble, you hear?

26:00.235 --> 26:01.402
You're already hurt.

26:04.872 --> 26:06.240
(BELLOWING)

26:06.841 --> 26:08.110
(GRUNTS)

26:11.079 --> 26:12.380
(GROANS)

26:13.314 --> 26:15.016
(GRUNTING)

26:15.683 --> 26:16.752
(SCREAMING)

26:25.560 --> 26:26.595
(SCREAMING)

26:33.001 --> 26:34.569
(CHOKING)

26:34.635 --> 26:36.238
(BELLOWING)

26:47.648 --> 26:49.283
(BELLOWING STOPS)

27:20.648 --> 27:22.184
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

28:51.718 --> 28:52.952
(LAUGHS)

28:55.822 --> 28:58.925
Oh, my husband is a charmer.

28:59.959 --> 29:01.894
If he were here, he'd have gone all out.

29:03.130 --> 29:05.364
A sweet drink for the lady.

29:06.598 --> 29:09.134
Then he'd sit and look you in the eye,

29:09.201 --> 29:10.737
and chat with you

29:10.804 --> 29:12.305
like you were the best of friends.

29:12.372 --> 29:13.270
For years.

29:14.074 --> 29:15.575
I am not my husband.

29:15.642 --> 29:17.600
So I'm just going
to give it to you straight.

29:18.243 --> 29:19.745
He wants to know
where those runners went...

29:19.812 --> 29:21.081
I don't know nothin', Miss Suzanna...

29:21.146 --> 29:23.682
Do not forget who you are,
where you are,

29:23.749 --> 29:25.637
and do not interrupt me again.

29:30.088 --> 29:31.190
Now...

29:31.257 --> 29:33.226
... my husband has cut into my day

29:33.291 --> 29:35.595
to appeal to you on his behalf.

29:35.662 --> 29:37.463
And though he wouldn't say it,

29:37.530 --> 29:40.399
he thinks you'll listen
because we are kin.

29:44.737 --> 29:45.971
But I know that's not going to work.

29:47.207 --> 29:49.080
So do you, I suspect.

29:50.308 --> 29:53.045
We may share blood,
but we are strangers,

29:53.112 --> 29:54.950
with nothing in common

29:55.347 --> 29:58.107
'cept a daddy who didn't
care about either of us.

29:58.550 --> 30:01.653
He did have a few sentimental
lapses, I suppose.

30:01.720 --> 30:04.002
He purchased you
a wedding gift, after all.

30:04.757 --> 30:06.426
What was your buck's name again?

30:09.563 --> 30:10.797
Moses.

30:12.797 --> 30:14.299
I've been told you put your body

30:14.366 --> 30:17.236
between that slave catcher's
bullet and your family.

30:19.005 --> 30:20.594
And your Moses...

30:21.441 --> 30:24.210
He just let you, didn't he?

30:26.078 --> 30:29.982
I cannot fathom men's
disregard for their children.

30:30.048 --> 30:33.286
They are only concerned with the
mark they'll leave on this world.

30:34.520 --> 30:36.088
Their legacy.

30:37.323 --> 30:39.603
Never knowing that very thing...

30:40.526 --> 30:42.962
... is tugging at their
pant-leg the whole time.

30:49.801 --> 30:51.484
These are papers.

30:52.037 --> 30:53.506
For you and your daughter.

30:56.808 --> 30:59.112
All they require is my husband's seal.

31:00.412 --> 31:02.347
He gives you what you want,
he gets what he wants,

31:02.414 --> 31:04.817
and I get to return
to my nursery in peace.

31:07.452 --> 31:09.087
- (DOOR OPENS)
- What about Moses?

31:09.154 --> 31:11.523
My husband's gonna need
his pound of flesh.

31:13.759 --> 31:15.222
Eat.

31:16.095 --> 31:18.464
And think about what's best
for your child.

31:23.970 --> 31:25.171
(DOOR CLOSES)

31:43.021 --> 31:44.523
ROSALEE: We gotta check that shoulder.

31:44.589 --> 31:46.291
- Ain't no time.
- How bad it hurt?

31:46.358 --> 31:48.727
I's fine. We still got a lot
of ground to cover. (PANTING)

31:48.795 --> 31:50.596
We don't tend to this,
only gonna get worse.

31:50.662 --> 31:52.198
(GRUNTS) Ain't no gettin' worse.

31:52.264 --> 31:54.033
And I don't need you lookin'
on me every two seconds.

31:54.099 --> 31:55.500
You ain't gonna fix this.

31:55.567 --> 31:56.903
There ain't no fixin' this.

31:56.970 --> 31:58.371
We gonna get to that train.

31:58.438 --> 32:01.207
And then what? We took off
without even looking back.

32:01.274 --> 32:02.508
And I don't know how
to look forward, either.

32:02.575 --> 32:04.643
Not without Pearly Mae.

32:04.710 --> 32:06.145
There ain't no goin' back.

32:06.778 --> 32:08.714
Not for any of us.

32:08.780 --> 32:11.688
I done looked to God
as far as I can remember.

32:11.951 --> 32:13.252
And he always hear me!

32:13.318 --> 32:14.335
Shh!

32:14.402 --> 32:16.121
He done brought me Pearly Mae

32:16.146 --> 32:17.879
when I needed her the
most, and then Boo...

32:17.922 --> 32:19.357
And he been real good to you, then.

32:19.424 --> 32:20.459
Not now, he ain't.

32:20.526 --> 32:22.495
Now he act like he can't even hear me!

32:22.562 --> 32:24.597
No matter how hard I pray.

32:25.565 --> 32:27.133
(GROANING)

32:30.702 --> 32:31.937
(GROANS)

32:36.842 --> 32:38.345
Look at me.

32:40.278 --> 32:42.981
I can't even pick up my baby girl.

32:47.051 --> 32:48.320
Look at her.

32:49.422 --> 32:50.516
Look at her!

32:51.390 --> 32:52.992
Go on now, I want you
to look her in the eyes

32:53.058 --> 32:54.527
and tell me what you see.

33:02.501 --> 33:04.436
(STAMMERS) I see Pearly Mae.

33:06.305 --> 33:08.283
Yeah, she got her mama's strength.

33:08.673 --> 33:09.742
And her daddy's.

33:11.076 --> 33:12.978
She ain't gonna need you
to carry her to freedom.

33:13.045 --> 33:14.447
She gonna carry you.

33:19.352 --> 33:21.659
My arm is hurting something awful.

33:22.822 --> 33:25.491
Uh, I saw some Devil's snare
a little while back.

33:25.557 --> 33:27.125
It gonna help with the swelling.

33:27.192 --> 33:28.460
Yeah, well, be quick.

33:29.562 --> 33:31.164
We got a train to catch.

33:48.146 --> 33:49.883
You got something you want to say?

33:50.382 --> 33:51.618
No, sir.

33:56.622 --> 33:58.291
(LEAVES RUSTLING)

33:58.356 --> 33:59.725
Wait here.

34:07.432 --> 34:09.335
We should have helped him.

34:38.154 --> 34:39.156
(SIGHS)

34:43.226 --> 34:44.428
I got your friend.

34:44.495 --> 34:45.661
- (GASPS)
- Don't be afraid. Don't be afraid.

34:45.728 --> 34:48.331
I run across these slave catchers.

34:48.399 --> 34:51.368
They was chaining up a runaway
about as big as a house.

34:51.435 --> 34:52.710
Tried to stop 'em.

34:53.735 --> 34:55.004
(PANTS) There was just too many of 'em.

34:55.071 --> 34:57.384
I figure they gotta be with you.

34:57.908 --> 34:59.142
Listen to me.

34:59.209 --> 35:01.479
It's just, uh, it's down the road,

35:01.544 --> 35:03.013
but if you're heading north...

35:04.415 --> 35:05.950
... you're going in the wrong direction.

35:08.852 --> 35:10.687
From where you stand...

35:10.754 --> 35:13.190
(PANTING)

35:13.256 --> 35:14.524
... you got two routes north.

35:14.591 --> 35:15.892
(GRUNTS)

35:15.959 --> 35:17.662
You got the Chelsea Savannah...

35:18.595 --> 35:20.964
... and the Ohio River.

35:21.031 --> 35:22.566
This time of year,
your best bet's the Ohio.

35:22.633 --> 35:24.301
She's low and easy to cross.

35:24.368 --> 35:25.869
And you'll find
a clear route to that river

35:25.935 --> 35:26.970
along the Blue Ridge Mountains.

35:27.937 --> 35:30.508
It's about three weeks on foot,

35:30.573 --> 35:32.776
- but you ought to be able to...
- "Blue haze."

35:34.711 --> 35:35.779
What'd you say?

35:37.580 --> 35:40.750
Them mountains you talking about.

35:40.817 --> 35:42.285
Yeah, Blue Ridge.

35:42.352 --> 35:43.855
Yeah, we...

35:44.955 --> 35:46.589
... we were heading that way.

35:46.656 --> 35:47.825
Good.

35:49.026 --> 35:51.761
Then we heard about a...

35:51.828 --> 35:52.830
... train...

35:54.297 --> 35:55.533
... taking off from Atlanta.

35:56.834 --> 35:57.745
That's smart.

35:58.868 --> 36:00.870
Travel time, you cut that in half.

36:00.937 --> 36:02.672
And when you cross that Ohio,

36:04.607 --> 36:07.477
there'll be far more people willing
to help you along the way.

36:07.544 --> 36:10.480
I don't know how you're gonna slip back
in the city without being seen, though.

36:14.084 --> 36:15.586
Unless I hide you in my wagon.

36:23.826 --> 36:25.129
(HORSE WHICKERS)

36:25.194 --> 36:26.397
It's okay, that's my son.

36:32.435 --> 36:33.877
- (GUN COCKS)
- BEN: Pa, we have to bring her back

36:33.902 --> 36:34.829
alive!

36:36.107 --> 36:37.475
Goddamn it.

36:37.540 --> 36:39.375
Get on in there, flush her out.

36:39.442 --> 36:40.578
(GASPING)

36:44.848 --> 36:46.750
(GASPING)

36:49.620 --> 36:51.288
(GROANS)

37:06.937 --> 37:08.306
(GROANING)

37:13.743 --> 37:15.912
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

37:15.979 --> 37:17.948
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)

37:20.216 --> 37:21.751
(SIGHING) Where they at?

37:21.817 --> 37:23.821
They was right behind us.

37:23.886 --> 37:25.888
HENRY: What about that gunshot we heard?

37:25.955 --> 37:27.024
They gonna be here.

37:28.125 --> 37:29.760
(LEAVES RUSTLING)

37:36.500 --> 37:38.068
Them catchers caught Zeke.

37:38.134 --> 37:40.169
HENRY: What happened?

37:40.236 --> 37:42.606
I did what I could, but them rednecks
was on him like a prize stag.

37:44.174 --> 37:45.977
HENRY: Hey, hey,
here come Moses and Boo.

37:50.580 --> 37:52.448
NOAH: Where's Rose?

37:52.515 --> 37:54.451
I don't know. She never came back.

37:57.953 --> 37:59.855
HENRY: We got to move.

37:59.922 --> 38:01.625
(LEAVES RUSTLING)

38:07.564 --> 38:08.865
(PANTING)

38:08.932 --> 38:10.667
I ran into the catcher and his boy.

38:10.734 --> 38:11.868
And you managed to get away?

38:11.935 --> 38:14.305
Yeah, but he know now, about the train.

38:18.975 --> 38:20.477
(STAMMERS) I thought
he was gonna help us.

38:20.544 --> 38:22.011
He gonna be lying in wait now.

38:22.078 --> 38:23.913
All we done to get to the damn train

38:23.980 --> 38:25.515
ruined by an empty-headed gal.

38:29.352 --> 38:31.754
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

38:31.821 --> 38:33.356
Now we find another way is all.

38:49.740 --> 38:52.237
Corra said Miss Suzanna offered
you and your baby freedom.

38:53.176 --> 38:55.312
You can't trust nothing that woman says.

38:55.379 --> 38:58.082
Miss Suzanna's a lot
of things, but she's honest.

38:58.149 --> 38:59.716
I sacrificed myself

38:59.783 --> 39:03.421
because I thought Moses was my
baby's best chance at freedom.

39:04.988 --> 39:06.524
But these here,

39:07.658 --> 39:10.694
this make me her best chance.

39:15.966 --> 39:18.134
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)

39:18.201 --> 39:19.368
AUGUST: Ben.

39:19.435 --> 39:21.138
BEN: Ain't no way we missed them.

39:23.372 --> 39:25.342
Maybe that slave girl was lying to you.

39:35.551 --> 39:37.120
- They're going at it from above.
- (GUN COCKS)

39:37.187 --> 39:38.354
Them papers could be fake.

39:38.421 --> 39:39.452
They ain't!

39:40.156 --> 39:41.457
I can read 'em.

39:41.524 --> 39:45.495
I stole one of Miss Suzanna hornbooks

39:45.562 --> 39:47.330
when we used to be playmates.

39:48.165 --> 39:49.433
Taught myself.

39:50.366 --> 39:51.669
They real.

39:52.268 --> 39:55.439
Just like this slaver bill
on master's desk.

